{"id": "EUVD-2024-36259", "enisaUuid": "7d65afc2-fb76-3968-9082-069412c3b731", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nblk-iocost: do not WARN if iocg was already offlined\n\nIn iocg_pay_debt(), warn is triggered if 'active_list' is empty, which\nis intended to confirm iocg is active when it has debt. However, warn\ncan be triggered during a blkcg or disk removal, if iocg_waitq_timer_fn()\nis run at that time:\n\n  WARNING: CPU: 0 PID: 2344971 at block/blk-iocost.c:1402 iocg_pay_debt+0x14c/0x190\n  Call trace:\n  iocg_pay_debt+0x14c/0x190\n  iocg_kick_waitq+0x438/0x4c0\n  iocg_waitq_timer_fn+0xd8/0x130\n  __run_hrtimer+0x144/0x45c\n  __hrtimer_run_queues+0x16c/0x244\n  hrtimer_interrupt+0x2cc/0x7b0\n\nThe warn in this situation is meaningless. Since this iocg is being\nremoved, the state of the 'active_list' is irrelevant, and 'waitq_timer'\nis canceled after removing 'active_list' in ioc_pd_free(), which ensures\niocg is freed after iocg_waitq_timer_fn() returns.\n\nTherefore, add the check if iocg was already offlined to avoid warn\nwhen removing a blkcg or disk.", "datePublished": "2024-05-30T15:29:07", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:30:10", "baseScore": 7.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1c172ac7afe4442964f4153b2c78fe4e005d9d67", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/14b3275f93d4a0d8ddc02195bc4e9869b7a3700e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/01bc4fda9ea0a6b52f12326486f07a4910666cf6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/aed0aac18f039dd4af13c143063754efca358cb0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/56a9d07f427378eeb75b917bb49c6fbea8204126", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7d215e013d097ed6fc4b0ad0272c9514214dc408"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-36908"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "012c19de-60c3-3dc4-b768-59f36615d62b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <01bc4fda9ea0a6b52f12326486f07a4910666cf6"}, {"id": "0b79a015-f95e-37a7-a48e-dcdbd626c525", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "243e8593-5cee-34d9-8810-d9b442bdb283", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.135"}, {"id": "50307b3f-3022-31f1-afc8-7ffb8f8c7510", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.237"}, {"id": "686239b8-c4f0-3500-bc01-7955a3f4c5b9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.9"}, {"id": "6d2a8c49-1875-353f-aaa5-c3535e072045", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.31"}, {"id": "6fe84229-1c83-3e36-a883-13f2bea8145e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.8.10"}, {"id": "7b877009-83a7-30ab-9bb2-ad7abec1aa0b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <56a9d07f427378eeb75b917bb49c6fbea8204126"}, {"id": "8c64b7b3-f054-341a-8742-8fa39732a869", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.181"}, {"id": "a431a717-02c7-3218-825f-dc5199d1c3ed", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.4"}, {"id": "a7b727e9-8d67-35c5-9c11-062f36c1baab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <7d215e013d097ed6fc4b0ad0272c9514214dc408"}, {"id": "c8740591-824a-3cbe-8262-538946050f46", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <aed0aac18f039dd4af13c143063754efca358cb0"}, {"id": "e0bfb95b-b504-3698-a7de-8f5be210a2f6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <1c172ac7afe4442964f4153b2c78fe4e005d9d67"}, {"id": "f24f0e2b-b886-3259-bbf3-33bea8becfe7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7caa47151ab2e644dd221f741ec7578d9532c9a3 <14b3275f93d4a0d8ddc02195bc4e9869b7a3700e"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "7716a053-6862-3462-a332-d3bfdd2033ce", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}